01:10:25,636 --> 01:10:30,641
Then he released 'em at 10.30. By that
time, his buddies were ready and waiting.

705
01:10:30,724 --> 01:10:33,644
No. Pell went with 'em that night.
I'm sure of it.

706
01:10:33,727 --> 01:10:35,229
Do you think he'll crack?

707
01:10:35,312 --> 01:10:38,357
Down here they say
rattlesnakes don't commit suicide.

708
01:10:48,075 --> 01:10:51,245
(Ward) Did you release
the three civil rights workers...

709
01:10:51,328 --> 01:10:54,998
..into the hands of the Klan
on the night of June 21st?

710
01:10:55,082 --> 01:10:56,208
No.

711
01:10:56,291 --> 01:10:59,336
- Are you a member of the Ku Klux Klan?
- No.

712
01:10:59,878 --> 01:11:03,590
- Have you ever been a member?
- No.

713
01:11:03,674 --> 01:11:06,760
Are you familiar with
the term Grand Cyclops?

714
01:11:06,843 --> 01:11:08,512
I've heard of it.

715
01:11:08,595 --> 01:11:12,432
Were you in fact the Grand Cyclops
of the East Mississippi Klavern...

716
01:11:12,516 --> 01:11:16,019
..of the White Knights of the Ku Klux Klan
for the past three years?

717
01:11:16,103 --> 01:11:20,232
Objection. My client's already told you,
he's not even a member of the Klan.

718
01:11:20,315 --> 01:11:25,320
Objection? This is just an interview, sir.
There's really no need to be so formal.

719
01:11:25,612 --> 01:11:31,952
Well, if this is just an interview, I guess
I don't have to stay here. I got work to do.

720
01:11:34,037 --> 01:11:38,541
- I guess you do too, don't you?
- Yes, sir. You can be sure that we'll do it.

721
01:11:39,167 --> 01:11:41,252
Good luck.

722
01:11:42,212 --> 01:11:46,966
Y'all get enough to indict me,
you know where to find me.

723
01:11:49,135 --> 01:11:50,970
- How'd it go?
- Fine. Just fine.

724
01:11:51,054 --> 01:11:53,598
Don't you worry about a goddamn thing.

725
01:11:54,682 --> 01:11:56,684
Are you about to be indicted?

726
01:11:56,768 --> 01:11:59,729
Does the FBI have evidence
against the sheriff's office?

727
01:11:59,813 --> 01:12:03,733
- Are you cooperating with them?
- We're cooperatin'. We have all along.

728
01:12:03,817 --> 01:12:05,777
There's not one iota of proof.

729
01:12:05,860 --> 01:12:09,906
Could you not do that, please?
Sir, do not do that, please.

730
01:12:11,241 --> 01:12:14,452
You've already been told once!
Get the fuck outta here!

731
01:12:14,535 --> 01:12:16,746
(screaming)

732
01:12:16,829 --> 01:12:20,458
Do we have to tell you 2,000 times?
Go back where you belong!

733
01:12:21,250 --> 01:12:23,670
Get outta my face!

734
01:12:23,753 --> 01:12:26,881
Get on outta here and leave us alone!
Leave us alone!

735
01:12:27,840 --> 01:12:30,968
Go on home where you belong, boy!
You're gonna get hurt!

736
01:12:33,429 --> 01:12:36,724
Mr Ward, this is gettin' to be
about as much as we can take.

737
01:12:36,808 --> 01:12:39,685
- I cannot register a stronger complaint.
- Not now, sir.

738
01:12:39,769 --> 01:12:44,565
Now, just a minute. I resent your
public pursuit of my sheriff's department.

739
01:12:44,649 --> 01:12:48,319
You have made every effort to
implicate them in these disappearances.

740
01:12:48,402 --> 01:12:53,240
Your slimy innuendoes are not evidence
that they were connected with any crime.

741
01:12:53,324 --> 01:12:56,202
We're trying to get to the truth.
We're frustrated too.

742
01:12:56,285 --> 01:12:59,664
Any jackass can point a finger,
but that ain't evidence.

743
01:12:59,747 --> 01:13:03,918
us old cotton-choppers are still
stupid enough to believe in democracy.

744
01:13:04,001 --> 01:13:08,631
- We know our rights under the law!
- You know somethin', all right.

745
01:13:08,714 --> 01:13:13,803
- I'd bet a cotton-choppin' dollar on that.
- You're gettin' so far up my nose,...

746
01:13:13,886 --> 01:13:16,847
..l'm beginnin' to feel
your boots on my chin.

747
01:13:16,931 --> 01:13:19,808
And I'm tellin' you one more time,
Mr Apple Red.

748
01:13:19,892 --> 01:13:24,521
A couple of crazies in bedsheets dancin'
round the countryside scarin' Negroes...

749
01:13:24,605 --> 01:13:27,608
..is not the fault of the entire
state of Mississippi!

750
01:13:27,691 --> 01:13:33,322
There are three dead kids and a lot of
scared people because of your sheriff.

751
01:13:33,405 --> 01:13:39,161
- So get used to havin' us around.
- Get used to my boots on your chin too.

752
01:13:39,244 --> 01:13:41,330
And you people better back off.

753
01:13:42,664 --> 01:13:47,419
Goddamn FBl. Who do they think they are,
comin' to my part of the country...

754
01:13:47,503 --> 01:13:50,923
- Do you have a statement, Mr Mayor?
- Goddamn right I have.

755
01:13:51,006 --> 01:13:53,800
For a moment there, Mr Anderson,...

756
01:13:53,884 --> 01:13:57,012
..it sounded like we were
both on the same side.

757
01:14:24,790 --> 01:14:27,417
- Are you all right, honey?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

758
01:14:27,501 --> 01:14:30,754
- Let me know if you need anything.
- Thanks. I will.

759
01:15:25,308 --> 01:15:27,393
(vehicle approaches)

760
01:15:55,338 --> 01:15:57,006
Momma! Come quick!

761
01:16:13,564 --> 01:16:16,692
There's no sign of him, sir.
He's long gone.

762
01:16:16,776 --> 01:16:20,571
His mother lives across the street.
She won't even answer the door.

763
01:16:20,654 --> 01:16:24,241
I want the whole area covered.
Someone must have seen something.

764
01:16:24,325 --> 01:16:26,577
- They won't talk to us.
- Get going, Mr Bird.

765
01:16:26,660 --> 01:16:29,455
If they won't talk to us, shake it out of 'em.

766
01:16:32,750 --> 01:16:35,252
(Bird) Let's go. Every house. Come on.

767
01:16:42,343 --> 01:16:44,094
What?

768
01:16:44,178 --> 01:16:49,892
All these white guys chasin' around with
their notebooks will get you nowhere.

769
01:16:49,975 --> 01:16:52,686
OK. What would you do?

770
01:16:57,941 --> 01:17:00,444
It's OK to be afraid.

771
01:17:08,243 --> 01:17:12,414
Go on, Willie. Tell 'em what you saw.

772
01:17:18,628 --> 01:17:20,714
(Ward whistles)

773
01:17:46,281 --> 01:17:49,117
(judge) The defendants will rise.

774
01:17:51,995 --> 01:17:55,123
In this country a man's home is his castle.

775
01:17:56,416 --> 01:18:00,962
That is one of the principles
by which this community survives.

776
01:18:01,046 --> 01:18:04,174
You men have done violence
to that principle.

777
01:18:04,257 --> 01:18:07,343
But I want you to know
that the court understands...

778
01:18:07,427 --> 01:18:11,931
..that the crimes you have committed
have been, to some extent at least,...

779
01:18:12,015 --> 01:18:15,810
..brought about by... outside influences.

780
01:18:15,894 --> 01:18:17,979
(murmuring)

781
01:18:24,694 --> 01:18:27,822
Outsiders have come
into Jessup County...

782
01:18:27,905 --> 01:18:32,243
..and they've been
people of low morality,...

783
01:18:32,327 --> 01:18:34,912
..and unhygienic.

784
01:18:35,246 --> 01:18:38,583
And their presence here
has provoked a lot of people.

785
01:18:38,666 --> 01:18:40,710
(murmuring)

786
01:18:41,294 --> 01:18:43,463
So the court understands,...

787
01:18:43,546 --> 01:18:47,216
..without condoning them, mind you,...

788
01:18:47,300 --> 01:18:50,428
..that the crimes to which
you men have pled guilty...

789
01:18:50,511 --> 01:18:56,017
..were, to some extent at least,
provoked by these outside influences.

790
01:18:58,519 --> 01:19:02,940
So, with all this,
I'm gonna make your punishment light.

791
01:19:03,941 --> 01:19:08,529
I'm gonna sentence you each
to five years' imprisonment.

792
01:19:11,615 --> 01:19:14,160
But I'm gonna suspend these sentences.

793
01:19:14,243 --> 01:19:16,328
(cheering)

794
01:19:48,861 --> 01:19:51,405
You can't go in there, sir.

795
01:19:51,488 --> 01:19:53,574
FBl. Let us through.

796
01:19:53,657 --> 01:19:56,076
I'm sorry, sir. You can't go in there.

797
01:20:01,498 --> 01:20:03,584
Sheriff?

798
01:20:06,795 --> 01:20:09,214
Y'all really started somethin' this time.

799
01:20:09,298 --> 01:20:11,842
Move these cars.
I wanna go in and talk to them.

800
01:20:11,925 --> 01:20:15,387
- You've gone as far as you're gonna go.
- We can handle this.

801
01:20:15,470 --> 01:20:18,390
Just some crazy coloureds
tearin' up their own assholes.

802
01:20:18,473 --> 01:20:20,559
Local problem.

803
01:20:36,491 --> 01:20:40,954
Look at those flames, Mr Ward. That's
why they sent you down here, wasn't it?

804
01:20:41,580 --> 01:20:45,000
It would've happened anyway
and you know it.

805
01:20:46,209 --> 01:20:49,796
If I was a Negro,
I'd probably think the same way they do.

806
01:20:50,255 --> 01:20:54,426
If you were a Negro,
nobody'd give a damn what you thought.

807
01:21:01,683 --> 01:21:03,768
(neighing)

808
01:21:51,357 --> 01:21:55,945
Aaron! Take your momma, grandmomma
and the children out the back door.

809
01:21:56,028 --> 01:22:00,408
When you hit the road, keep goin'.
You understand? Keep goin', son.

810
01:22:02,034 --> 01:22:04,412
Nathan! Come on, Nathan. Get up!

811
01:22:04,495 --> 01:22:07,623
Get up, Nathan, now! Come on!
Get out of the bed!

812
01:22:07,707 --> 01:22:12,211
- (Nathan) What's happening?
- Momma! Come on, Momma.

813
01:22:14,880 --> 01:22:16,966
Come on, y'all.

814
01:22:17,758 --> 01:22:20,511
Come on, Grandma. Let's go!

815
01:22:20,594 --> 01:22:23,723
(' "Try Jesus" by Vesta Williams)

816
01:22:28,477 --> 01:22:36,193
#All ye who labour

817
01:22:36,610 --> 01:22:41,699
Who's there? If you're in there,
come on out! You hear?

818
01:22:42,491 --> 01:22:44,702
I ain't takin' this shit no more!

819
01:22:59,550 --> 01:23:07,933
#Bring him your burdens

820
01:23:09,518 --> 01:23:15,357
#Seek not his favour

821
01:23:16,108 --> 01:23:24,199
#Tell... tell him your sorrows

822
01:23:25,701 --> 01:23:36,128
#In... him... confide

823
01:23:38,713 --> 01:23:42,634
#He satisfies

824
01:23:43,468 --> 01:23:47,389
#He satisfies

825
01:23:49,683 --> 01:23:51,643
Everything's OK, Papa.

826
01:23:52,018 --> 01:23:54,104
Momma and the girls are fine.

827
01:23:54,187 --> 01:23:57,691
They just cracked your head some.
You just keep on breathin'.

828
01:23:57,774 --> 01:23:59,943
Don't you go dyin' on me now.

829
01:24:00,151 --> 01:24:02,237
You hear me?

830
01:24:03,488 --> 01:24:05,490
You gonna be just fine.

831
01:24:32,350 --> 01:24:37,522
You know, cows won't run away. No one
knows why. They're just stupid, I guess.

832
01:24:37,605 --> 01:24:43,236
They just stand there until
their bellies swell up and they pop.

833
01:24:43,319 --> 01:24:46,114
They have relatives in Detroit.

834
01:24:46,906 --> 01:24:50,451
- Are they gonna go?
- I didn't give 'em any choice.

835
01:24:51,994 --> 01:24:55,123
(Anderson) At least we know who did this.

836
01:24:55,206 --> 01:24:58,042
- We did.
- Well, don't fret. It's progress.

837
01:24:58,126 --> 01:25:02,547
20 years ago they'd have
strung 'em up for stealin' a watermelon.

838
01:25:02,630 --> 01:25:06,050
I don't understand you, Mr Anderson.
Not at all.

839
01:25:07,468 --> 01:25:09,929
Let's get somethin' straight, all right?

840
01:25:10,012 --> 01:25:14,141
This thing was fucked up the moment
we turned it into a show for the newsmen.

841
01:25:14,225 --> 01:25:16,852
The moment those three kids
disappeared, it was news.

842
01:25:16,936 --> 01:25:21,273
The moment the three civil rights
workers disappeared, it was news.

843
01:25:21,357 --> 01:25:24,777
To me they're just kids.
They're still missin'.

844
01:25:24,860 --> 01:25:29,407
What's missing... is the 50 minutes
Pell said he was with his wife.

845
01:25:33,244 --> 01:25:35,329
OK.

846
01:25:51,011 --> 01:25:53,889
I love Mississippi.

847
01:26:04,691 --> 01:26:06,485
They...

848
01:26:06,568 --> 01:26:08,821
They hate Mississippi.

849
01:26:09,655 --> 01:26:13,450
They hate us because
we present a shining example...

850
01:26:13,534 --> 01:26:16,787
..of successful segregation.

851
01:26:16,870 --> 01:26:21,416
These Northern students,
with their atheist, communist bosses,...

852
01:26:21,500 --> 01:26:25,671
..that have come into our community
this summer with the wish to destroy it,...

853
01:26:25,754 --> 01:26:29,383
..this week have taken a terrible blow.

854
01:26:30,217 --> 01:26:33,929
This week their cause has been crippled.

855
01:26:34,012 --> 01:26:38,809
This week all of these federal policemen
you see out here pryin' into our lives,...

856
01:26:38,892 --> 01:26:40,852
..violatin' our civil liberties,...

857
01:26:40,936 --> 01:26:43,772
..have learned that they are
powerless against us...

858
01:26:43,855 --> 01:26:49,402
..if every single Anglo-Saxon
Christian one of us stands together!

859
01:26:54,741 --> 01:26:55,951
This week...

860
01:26:57,452 --> 01:26:59,829
- Ward?
- We have company, sir.

861
01:27:00,997 --> 01:27:03,333
Why are you here?
This is a political meeting.

862
01:27:03,416 --> 01:27:07,671
- Doesn't smell that way to me, Deputy.
- It's a political meeting, Hoover boy.

863
01:27:07,754 --> 01:27:13,343
Oh, it looks like a political meeting
but smells more like Klan to me,...

864
01:27:13,426 --> 01:27:16,721
..with or without the Halloween costumes.

865
01:27:17,472 --> 01:27:19,182
Gentlemen.

866
01:27:19,265 --> 01:27:22,894
In the courts of Mississippi,
they have been reminded...

867
01:27:22,977 --> 01:27:26,231
..that they cannot by force
turn our communities...

868
01:27:26,314 --> 01:27:28,817
..into replicas of theircommunities.

869
01:27:28,900 --> 01:27:33,363
Communities in which Negroes run riot,
unrestrained and unpunished,...

870
01:27:33,446 --> 01:27:37,784
..as they do this summer in the streets
of Harlem, or in the streets of Oakland,...

871
01:27:37,867 --> 01:27:40,036
..or in the streets of Chicago!

872
01:28:48,646 --> 01:28:50,731
(knocks)

873
01:29:01,283 --> 01:29:03,577
Can I come in?

874
01:29:12,044 --> 01:29:14,213
It's not good for you to be here.

875
01:29:14,296 --> 01:29:17,007
- Why?
- It's ugly.

876
01:29:17,925 --> 01:29:20,219
This whole thing is so ugly.

877
01:29:21,261 --> 01:29:25,015
Have you any idea what it's like
to live with all this?

878
01:29:25,891 --> 01:29:30,479
People look at us...
and only see bigots and racists.

879
01:29:32,731 --> 01:29:35,859
Hatred isn't something you're born with.

880
01:29:35,943 --> 01:29:38,028
It gets taught.

881
01:29:39,780 --> 01:29:43,742
At school they said segregation
is what it said in the Bible.

882
01:29:45,118 --> 01:29:48,997
Genesis 9, verse 27.

883
01:29:52,167 --> 01:29:57,088
At seven years of age, you get
told it enough times, you believe it.

884
01:29:59,090 --> 01:30:01,218
You believe the hatred.

885
01:30:02,260 --> 01:30:05,972
You live it. You breathe it.

886
01:30:08,099 --> 01:30:10,185
You marry it.

887
01:30:40,590 --> 01:30:43,176
My husband drove
one of the cars that night.

888
01:30:43,259 --> 01:30:46,679
- Shh.
- That's what you wanna hear, isn't it?

889
01:30:48,598 --> 01:30:53,728
(sobbing) The bodies are buried
on the Roberts farm, in an earthen dam.

890
01:31:12,246 --> 01:31:13,915
Sir!

891
01:31:26,636 --> 01:31:28,971
Take a break, Mr Bird.

892
01:31:29,055 --> 01:31:31,766
Put some handkerchiefs around your face.

893
01:31:35,644 --> 01:31:37,730
(Bird retches)

894
01:31:45,070 --> 01:31:47,156
Bring that here.

895
01:32:01,587 --> 01:32:05,090
The bodies of the three civil rights
workers were found today...

896
01:32:05,174 --> 01:32:07,551
..at an undisclosed grave.

897
01:32:08,969 --> 01:32:13,515
Neither the FBI nor the sheriff's
department will comment on the case.

898
01:32:13,599 --> 01:32:16,351
The bodies were brought
to Jessup County Hospital.

899
01:32:16,435 --> 01:32:18,937
Officials here also refused comment.

900
01:32:19,021 --> 01:32:23,358
There is speculation that an autopsy
will be performed later tonight.

901
01:32:25,486 --> 01:32:28,363
OK, keep it open. We're comin' through.

902
01:32:28,447 --> 01:32:31,116
Come on, open it up.

903
01:32:32,242 --> 01:32:34,161
Hold it back.

904
01:32:54,056 --> 01:32:56,933
Clinton,
you got problems at home to tend to.

905
01:32:57,017 --> 01:32:58,560
What do you mean?

906
01:32:58,643 --> 01:33:02,314
I mean pull your head
out of your ass and get home!

907
01:33:02,397 --> 01:33:06,902
"I, Vincent Thompson, am the
cheddar-cheese champion ofthe world."

908
01:33:08,111 --> 01:33:13,533
"In international competition with 42 other
entries, my cheddar won fiirstprize...

909
01:33:13,617 --> 01:33:17,412
..based on flavour, texture,
appearance and colour."

910
01:33:22,334 --> 01:33:26,004
Hey, Clinton.
I didn't expect you home so early.

911
01:33:27,255 --> 01:33:29,424
Hi, Frank.

912
01:33:40,059 --> 01:33:42,353
No, don't. I'm sorry.

913
01:33:45,190 --> 01:33:47,901
(punching)

914
01:33:47,984 --> 01:33:50,403
(Mrs Pell moans)

915
01:33:56,117 --> 01:33:58,202
Sir.

916
01:34:00,288 --> 01:34:02,373
Say again?

917
01:34:03,708 --> 01:34:05,793
I'll be right there.

918
01:34:10,590 --> 01:34:12,925
- Mr Bird.
- Yes, sir?

919
01:34:13,009 --> 01:34:15,094
Get five men and meet me outside.

920
01:34:17,472 --> 01:34:20,600
- Where's Anderson?
- He's at the motel, sir.

921
01:34:25,271 --> 01:34:29,358
You two take the front door. If anyone
tries to get past you, break 'em down.

922
01:34:29,442 --> 01:34:32,403
You two take the door on the corridor.
Mr Bird?

923
01:34:34,113 --> 01:34:38,117
OK. Go get Anderson. Bring him here.

924
01:34:38,200 --> 01:34:42,997
Don't tell him why.
Don't tell him anything. Just get him here.

925
01:34:58,429 --> 01:35:01,140
(footsteps)

926
01:35:14,320 --> 01:35:16,530
Mr Anderson. Stop!

927
01:35:16,613 --> 01:35:18,282
- Mr Anderson!
- Go to hell.

928
01:35:18,365 --> 01:35:21,910
I'm telling you to stop and
I mean it. We're not killers.

929
01:35:21,994 --> 01:35:26,081
- It's the difference between them and us.
- No, between them and you!

930
01:35:26,165 --> 01:35:28,542
- You're no more like them than I am.
- Wrong.

931
01:35:28,625 --> 01:35:32,212
What do you care what I do to a bastard
hidin' behind a sheriff's badge?

932
01:35:32,296 --> 01:35:35,424
- You have the whole world to change!
- And I'm changin' it.

933
01:35:35,507 --> 01:35:39,094
- You're as arrogant as you are stupid!
- You're changin' it too.

934
01:35:39,177 --> 01:35:41,179
I'll make some changes right now!

935
01:35:41,263 --> 01:35:45,642
Don't mess this up just because
